New charges: Alleged 'Hollywood Ripper' Michael Gargiulo, 35, is now accused of killing a young woman in Chicago in 1993

A man tagged the 'Hollywood Ripper' who is suspected of killing the former girlfriend of actor Ashton Kutcher has been charged with murdering another woman 18 years ago.

Air conditioner repairman Michael Gargiulo, 35, is already facing trial over the violent stabbing deaths of two female victims.

Now investigators in Chicago claim he also stabbed Tricia Pacaccio to death after she returned home after a night out with friends in 1993.

Prosecutors say the killing shows a similar pattern to the February2001 slaying of 22-year-old Ashley Ellerin, who was then Mr Kutcher’s girlfriend.

The actor, now married to Demi Moore, told Los Angeles police that Miss Ellerin never came to the door when he went to her Hollywood Hills home to pick her up to go to a post-Grammy Awards party.

Her bloodstained body was found later inside the house.

